r education, artistic creativity, solitude, and the contrast between lifestyles in a quiet Black Forest village and in a noisy contemporary United States. Forty-one black-and-white photographs taken by the author accompany and enliven the text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFeral catszGermanyzBlack Forest. 0aHuman-animal relationshipszGermanyzBlack Forest. 0aSolitudezGermanyzBlack Forest. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aLiterature : American Literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPsychology : Psychoanalysis. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Essays.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848850940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438488509423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438488509/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles